                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Aug. 5 (PTI): Idea Cellular has issued 3,640 connections to a single person and his company, Parliament was informed today.          
	The department of telecom report said most of the connections had been rented out to other customers. This could endanger national security, minister of state for telecom and IT Sachin Pilot said in a written reply to the Rajya Sabha.                  
	Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): Downward trend in enrolment in government and aided schools continues in Kerala, with the latest head-count showing a decline of 2.5 lakh pupils from last year. The reasons being cited is the proliferation of unaided schools and the increasing trend of parents sending their wards to English-medium schools.                  
	Gopeshwar (PTI): Five members of a family, including three children, were buried alive when a house collapsed in landslides triggered by heavy rain in Gopeshwar, Uttarakhand, on Thursday. The chief minister has asked the district administration to provide compensation to the next of kin of the deceased.                  
	Lucknow (PTI): A college student was found dead under mysterious circumstances on Wednesday near a swimming pool following which his mother lodged a complaint against two of his fellow students. The students have been taken into custody, police said.                  
	Dehra Dun (PTI): Doctors of government hospitals in Uttarakhand have threatened to go on an indefinite strike from Friday protesting against the appointment of an IAS officer in the health directorate.                                                                                                                                              
